From: Vladimir Yakovlev <vovchkir@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 3 Mar 2026 01:20:17 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] spi: spi-dw-dma: fix print error log when wait finish
 transaction
Git-commit: 3b46d61890632c8f8b117147b6923bff4b42ccb7
Patch-mainline: v7.0-rc3
References: CVE-2026-31560 bsc#1263057

If an error occurs, the device may not have a current message. In this
case, the system will crash.

In this case, it's better to use dev from the struct ctlr (struct spi_controller*).

Signed-off-by: Vladimir Yakovlev <vovchkir@gmail.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20260302222017.992228-2-vovchkir@gmail.com
Signed-off-by: Mark Brown <broonie@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 drivers/spi/spi-dw-dma.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/spi/spi-dw-dma.c
+++ b/drivers/spi/spi-dw-dma.c
@@ -231,7 +231,7 @@ static int dw_spi_dma_wait(struct dw_spi
 					 msecs_to_jiffies(ms));
 
 	if (ms == 0) {
-		dev_err(&dws->master->cur_msg->spi->dev,
+		dev_err(&dws->master->dev,
 			"DMA transaction timed out\n");
 		return -ETIMEDOUT;
 	}
